I further believe that the letter was sent by post, based upon the usual AGS office procedure for sending correspondence by post, which is as follows: 




 7.1. the solicitor signs the correspondence;
 7.2. the solicitor gives the signed correspondence to his or her legal assistant and requests that this be sent to the addressee by post;
 7.3. the legal assistant makes a photocopy of the signed correspondence and places the photocopy on the file.
